<td colspan="2" class="" style="text-align:center; font-size: 125%; font-weight: bold; background-color: mediumorchid">Nowrūz</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2" class="" style="text-align:center;"><a href="/wiki/File:Fr%C3%BChling_bl%C3%BChender_Kirschenbaum.jpg" class="image" title="Nowrūz"><img alt="Nowrūz" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/Fr%C3%BChling_bl%C3%BChender_Kirschenbaum.jpg/250px-Fr%C3%BChling_bl%C3%BChender_Kirschenbaum.jpg" width="250" height="188" border="0" /></a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="">Also called</th>
<td class="" style="">Also spelled Norouz, Narooz, Nawruz, Newroz, Newruz, Nauruz, Nawroz, Noruz, Novruz, Nauroz, Navroz, Naw-Rúz, Nowroj, Navroj, Nevruz, Neyruz <span class="Unicode">Наврӯз</span>, Navruz, Navrez, Nooruz, Nauryz, Nowrouz,</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="">Observed by</th>
<td class="" style="">Principally in <a href="/wiki/Iran" title="Iran">Iran</a>, <a href="/wiki/Tajikistan" title="Tajikistan">Tajikistan</a>, <a href="/wiki/Afghanistan" title="Afghanistan">Afghanistan</a>, <a href="/wiki/Azerbaijan" title="Azerbaijan">Azerbaijan</a>, as well as <a href="/wiki/Zoroastrian" title="Zoroastrian" class="mw-redirect">Zoroastrians</a>, <a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith" title="Bahá'í Faith">Bahá'ís</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Iranian_citizens_abroad" title="Iranian citizens abroad">Iranian diaspora</a> and other <a href="/wiki/Iranian_peoples" title="Iranian peoples">Iranian peoples</a> (including <a href="/wiki/Kurds" title="Kurds" class="mw-redirect">Kurds</a>) everywhere. Also observed in <a href="/wiki/Albania" title="Albania">Albania</a>, <a href="/wiki/Georgia_(country)" title="Georgia (country)">Georgia</a>, <a href="/wiki/Bosnia_and_Herzegovina" title="Bosnia and Herzegovina">Bosnia</a>, <a href="/wiki/Caucasus" title="Caucasus">Caucasus</a>, <a href="/wiki/Crimea" title="Crimea">Crimea</a>, <a href="/wiki/Kashmir" title="Kashmir">Kashmir</a>, <a href="/wiki/Kazakhstan" title="Kazakhstan">Kazakhstan</a>, <a href="/wiki/Kosovo" title="Kosovo">Kosovo</a>, <a href="/wiki/Kyrgyzstan" title="Kyrgyzstan">Kyrgyzstan</a>, <a href="/wiki/India" title="India">India</a>, <a href="/wiki/Iraq" title="Iraq">Iraq</a>, <a href="/wiki/Republic_of_Macedonia" title="Republic of Macedonia">Macedonia</a>, <a href="/wiki/Pakistan" title="Pakistan">Pakistan</a>, <a href="/wiki/Syria" title="Syria">Syria</a>, <a href="/wiki/Turkmenistan" title="Turkmenistan">Turkmenistan</a>, <a href="/wiki/Uzbekistan" title="Uzbekistan">Uzbekistan</a>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="">Significance</th>
<td class="" style="">New year holiday</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="">Date</th>
<td class="" style="">March 20th, 21st or 22nd. Some communities celebrate on the actual Spring Equinox. Others celebrated on a fixed day every year.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="">2009 date</th>
<td class="" style=""><a href="/wiki/Friday" title="Friday">Friday</a>, <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2009-03-20"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="03-20"><a href="/wiki/March_20" title="March 20">March 20</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/2009" title="2009">2009</a></span> at 11:44 <a href="/wiki/UTC" title="UTC" class="mw-redirect">UTC</a> <a href="/wiki/Equinox" title="Equinox">*</a></td>
